01/08/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The state anti-corruption commission called on new members of parliament Monday (31 July) to prepare and submit asset statements, in line with the law on preventing corruption. All newly-elected or appointed officials, among others in state institutions, are required to report on personal and family assets and property within 30 days of election. The statements are submitted to the anti-corruption commission and the Public Revenues Bureau. (Vecer - 01/08/06; Makfax - 31/07/06)
